libffcall - foreign function call libraries

This is a collection of four libraries which can be used to build
foreign function call interfaces in embedded interpreters.

The four packages are:

    avcall - calling C functions with variable arguments

    vacall - C functions accepting variable argument prototypes

    trampoline - closures as first-class C functions

    callback - closures with variable arguments as first-class C functions
               (a reentrant combination of vacall and trampoline)


Installation instructions:

        mkdir builddir
        cd builddir
        ../configure --cache-file=config.cache
        make
        make check
        make install


Note: It is possible to do a build that produces shared libraries (by
passing --enable-shared to configure), but it makes little sense to do so:

1) The main function here is compiled from non-PIC assembly language.
   I.e. relocations would remain. The GNU linker supports shared libraries
   with relocations on x86 systems. But only on x86!

2) It is an overkill: libavcall, libvacall, libcallback have less than 6 KB
   of executable code:

$ size libavcall.a
   text    data     bss     dec     hex filename
    383       0       0     383     17f avcall-i386.o (ex libavcall.a)
   1132       0       0    1132     46c avcall-libapi.o (ex libavcall.a)
    131       0       0     131      83 avcall-structcpy.o (ex libavcall.a)
$ size libvacall.a
   text    data     bss     dec     hex filename
    365       0       0     365     16d vacall.o (ex libvacall.a)
   2297       4       0    2301     8fd vacall-libapi.o (ex libvacall.a)
    131       0       0     131      83 vacall-structcpy.o (ex libvacall.a)
$ size libcallback.a
   text    data     bss     dec     hex filename
    395       0       0     395     18b vacall-i386.o (ex libcallback.a)
   2297       0       0    2297     8f9 vacall-libapi.o (ex libcallback.a)
    131       0       0     131      83 vacall-structcpy.o (ex libcallback.a)
   1454       0      44    1498     5da trampoline.o (ex libcallback.a)
    340       0       0     340     154 callback-libapi.o (ex libcallback.a)
    573       0       0     573     23d lock.o (ex libcallback.a)
      0       0       0       0       0 threadlib.o (ex libcallback.a)

When a shared library is loaded, you spend at least 4 KB for its code,
data and BSS. This is overkill for such a tiny library.


Files in this package:

    Documentation:

        README          this text
        COPYING         free software license
        PLATFORMS       list of supported platforms

    Source:

        avcall/*        the avcall package
        vacall/*        the vacall package
        trampoline/*    the trampoline package
        callback/*      the callback package

    Building:

        configure       configuration script
        configure.ac    autoconf source for the configuration script
        m4/*            auxiliary configuration scripts
        Makefile.in     Makefile master


